Indian Equity Movers: Kinetic Motor and UTV Software

-- B y   S h i k h a r   B a l w a n i   a n d   H e m a l   S a v a i
-- 
2011-12-08T10:28:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/indian-equity-movers-kec-international-kinetic-utv-software.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual (SENSEX)  moves in  Indian trading. (BSE100)  Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 3:30 p.m. close in Mumbai.  The BSE India Sensitive Index, or Sensex, sank 2.3 percent
to 16,488.24, the most since Nov. 21. The  BSE-200 Index (BSE200)  lost 2.2
percent to 1,994.45.  Kinetic Motor Co. (KNH)   climbed 3.1 percent to 15.15
rupees, its highest close since Nov. 18. The board of  Kinetic
Engineering Ltd. (KNEL)   will meet tomorrow to consider a
possible merger of Kinetic Motor into Kinetic Engineering,
according to an exchange filing. Kinetic Engineering rose 0.9
percent to 99.85 rupees.  UTV Software Communications Ltd. (UTV)   surged 3.1
percent to 980.55 rupees, the highest close in three months.
 India ’s government has approved Walt Disney’s plan to raise its
stake in the movie and television content maker to 100 percent
from 48 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
